This paper discusses the use of memristors in neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on the use of unipolar memristors, which are a type of electronic device, and therefore could also fall under the categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). The paper also discusses the use of spiking neural networks, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence and robotics (cs.AR) or systems and control (cs.SY).
